[[File:Sierra Ancha dwellings.jpg|300px|thumb|Cliff dwellings in the Sierra Anchas.]]
The '''Sierra Ancha Cliff Dwellings''' are a series of [[Pre-Columbian era|Pre-Columbian]] [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|native American]] [[cliff-dwelling]]s located in the [[Sierra Ancha Wilderness]]. They were built between 1280 and 1350 by the [[Salado culture|Salado]] people. The Sierra Ancha is home to several prominent ruin sites known as the Devil's Chasm Fortress, the Canyon Creek Ruins, the Pueblo Canyon Ruins, the Cold Springs Canyon Ruins, and the Cooper Forks Canyon Ruins. Collectively they have been called the Cherry Creek Ruins.<ref>http://www.statemuseum.arizona.edu/research/final_sierra_ancha_rpt.shtml</ref>
